    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Helsinki University Central Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pancreatic resections carry a high risk for complications, especially pancreatic fistula.
      Both hydrocortisone and pasireotide have been shown to be effective in reducing complications
      in earlier RCTs. The aim of this study is to compare the effectiveness and safety of these
      two drugs in preventing complications of pancreatic surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
